The course provides practical skills for planning and presenting academic research, improves the learners' skills of using academic literature and databases, improves the learners' knowledge of orthography, and oral and written presentation skills.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course expands the knowledge about Estonian ortography, oral and written skills of presentation, and the skills of writing different types of texts. The learner will acquire basic knowledge, terminology and practical skills to plan research and write it according to requirements. The learners explore the principles of the philosophy of science, research methods and work with academic literature and databases.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) compile texts proceeding from the process-based principles of writing, use proper references and citations; 2) assess their use of language critically and correct it, if necessary; 3) compile academic texts and follow the principles of public speaking; 4) be aware of the principles of the philosophy and ethics of research; 5) know research methods, the methods of data collection, and data analysis; 6) compile a research plan and present their research findings according to the requirements.
